>
>Since it is a 6 volt gauge(?) Do I nee to replace it wiht a 12 volt gauge?
>I have found aftermarket sending unit/fuel gauge 12 volts units that are
>the same size as the 66 gauge, is this the way to go?

In the '67 parts manual at the doc project, on page 581, the same
sending unit is listed for 6 V and 12 V.  The 6 V and 12 V gauges
have different part numbers.  The gauge should match the system
voltage of the Bus, but the sender should work for either voltage.

Matt Roberds
